ling requirement while preserving the existing process structure and most of the original business behavior. It allows both assessment activities to contribute to the rejection decision, but ensures that once assessment_status becomes \\\"rejected\\\", it cannot be overwritten before the exclusive branch that informs the donor and terminates the process.\",\n  \"alternative_suggestion\": {\n    \"reason\": \"A more explicit control-flow repair would require inserting a complete conditional branch after each activity that can set assessment_status to \\\"rejected\\\". The provided operations do not support inserting a full XOR structure with a multi-activity branch containing both \\\"inform of rejection\\\" and \\\"terminate\\\" while preserving the existing continuation path.\",\n    \"conceptual_solution\": \"After each activity that may set assessment_status to \\\"rejected\\\", insert an XOR decision: if assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\", execute \\\"inform of rejection\\\" followed directly by \\\"terminate\\\"; otherwise continue with the normal assessment flow.\",\n    \"expected_compliance_impact\": \"This would fully satisfy the requirement because every point at which the rejected condition can become true would be followed by the required rejection notification and immediate termination.\"\n  }\n}",
